{% comment %}
  Inline icon set for quiz answer cards.

  Client note (2026-07-21): the icons must READ AS THE ACTUAL ITEM — the
  generic library set had a lab flask standing in for a plastic water bottle,
  a drinking glass for a protein shaker, an archive box for a glass jar, and
  the identical 3D box for both "container" and "packaged food". Those are
  now purpose-drawn: silhouettes a shopper recognises at a glance rather than
  the nearest available generic glyph. Icons that were already literal
  (microwave, fish, shirt, receipt, droplet) are unchanged.

  24×24 viewBox, 1.7px stroke — a hair lighter than the old 2px because the
  drawn shapes carry more internal detail at the 26px chip size.

  Duotone: each icon carries a .qi-fill path UNDER its outline holding the
  vessel's contents (water, coffee, food, laundry). Styled in the quiz
  section stylesheet, it inherits currentColor so it reads correctly both on
  the tinted chip and on the solid-accent selected state. A filled mass
  resolves much faster than a pure outline at 26px.

  Usage: {% render 'tamarinse-quiz-icon', icon: 'bottle' %}
{% endcomment %}

<svg
  class="tamarinse-quiz-icon"
  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
  width="26"
  height="26"
  fill="none"
  stroke="currentColor"
  stroke-width="1.7"
  stroke-linecap="round"
  stroke-linejoin="round"
  aria-hidden="true"
  focusable="false"
>
  {%- case icon -%}
    {%- when 'bottle' -%}
